The discussion focused on improving James' Research Statement for his tenure review dossier. Arachne provided suggestions to enhance the flow, clarity, and impact of the statement. Arachne emphasized simplifying long sentences, using active voice, and making key contributions more visible. The revised statement highlighted James' interdisciplinary research, collaborative approach, and use of quantitative techniques. It underscored his efforts to bridge the divide between climate science, biophysical modeling, and climate economics, as well as his contribution to quantifying climate risks and calculating the "social cost of carbon." Arachne also emphasized James' comprehensive understanding of food production and his long-term goal of integrating insights and models for managing complex, social-environmental systems. The importance of clear and concise communication that highlights the impact and significance of James' work was reiterated.
